# Copy to .env and fill in what you want to pin. `make install-router` /
# scripts/install-router.sh auto-loads this file if present.
#
#   cp .env.example .env && edit .env && make install-router
#
# Everything here is OPTIONAL: anything left blank is resolved at runtime —
# ROUTER_HOST is auto-detected from your machine's default gateway, and
# ROUTER_USER / ROUTER_PASSWORD are asked interactively.

# Router host. Leave blank to auto-detect the default gateway (the LAN router).
# ROUTER_HOST=192.168.1.1

# Router admin credentials. Leave blank to be prompted (login defaults to admin).
# ROUTER_USER=admin
# ROUTER_PASSWORD=

# Other optional overrides (see scripts/install-router.sh header for all knobs)
# ROUTER_PORT=22
# ROUTER_LISTEN=0.0.0.0:9091
# ROUTER_OPKG_UUID=auto
